          br
          p panX is a software package for comprehensive pan-genome analysis and web-based interactive visualization and dynamic exploration.
          p It encompasses various interconnected viewers, allows rapid search via gene name, diversity, duplications, annotation, integrates strain-associated meta-data (collection data, country, resistance, etc.), gene presence/absence pattern, gene gain/loss event on phylogeny.
          p panX helps users to gain insights into bacterial genomic diversity and the dynamics of the accessory genes linked with habitat adaptation, antibiotic resistance, virulence, as well as epidemiological markers.
